assistant:
To use a variable in a message:
```
define user_name = varchar(50);
let user_name = 'John';
message 'Welcome, ' || user_name || '!';
```
This will display a personalized welcome message using the user_name variable.

To display a message with numeric values:
```
define total_items = integer;
define total_cost = money;
let total_items = 5;
let total_cost = 100.50;
message 'You have ' || char(total_items) || ' items, totaling $' || char(total_cost);
```
This will show a message with the number of items and total cost.

Here's how to use a message for debugging:
```
define debug_flag = integer;
let debug_flag = 1;
if debug_flag = 1 then
    message 'Debug: Entering process_data() function';
endif;
```
This will display a debug message only when the debug flag is set.

To display a database operation result:
```
define rows_affected = integer;
select count(*) into :rows_affected from customers where status = 'Active';
message 'Number of active customers: ' || char(rows_affected);
```
This will show the number of active customers retrieved from the database.

Here's an error handling scenario using a message:
```
define error_code = integer;
if error_code != 0 then
    message 'An error occurred. Error code: ' || char(error_code) || '. Please contact support.';
endif;
```
This will display an error message with the error code when an error occurs.

Here's how to display application status:
```
define app_status = varchar(20);
define last_update = date;
let app_status = 'Running';
let last_update = today;
message 'Application Status: ' || app_status || '
' ||
        'Last Updated: ' || char(last_update);
```
This will show a pop-up with the current application status and last update date.
